{"schema_version":"1.6.0","id":"OESA-2021-1370","modified":"2021-09-30T11:31:09Z","published":"2021-09-30T11:31:09Z","related":["CVE-2021-3658"],"summary":"bluez security update","details":"This package provides all utilities for use in Bluetooth applications. The BLUETOOTH trademarks are owned by Bluetooth SIG, Inc., U.S.A.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nbluetoothd from bluez incorrectly saves adapters&apos; Discoverable status when a device is powered down, and restores it when powered up. If a device is powered down while discoverable, it will be discoverable when powered on again. This could lead to inadvertent exposure of the bluetooth stack to physically nearby attackers.(CVE-2021-3658)","affected":[{"package":{"ecosystem":"openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1","name":"bluez","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/bluez&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0","fixed":"5.54-5.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["bluez-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bluez-debugsource-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bluez-devel-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bluez-debuginfo-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bluez-cups-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bluez-libs-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["bluez-help-5.54-5.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["bluez-5.54-5.oe1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["bluez-5.54-5.oe1.x86_64.rpm","bluez-devel-5.54-5.oe1.x86_64.rpm","bluez-debuginfo-5.54-5.oe1.x86_64.rpm","bluez-cups-5.54-5.oe1.x86_64.rpm","bluez-debugsource-5.54-5.oe1.x86_64.rpm","bluez-libs-5.54-5.oe1.x86_64.rpm"]}},{"package":{"ecosystem":"openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2","name":"bluez","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/bluez&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0","fixed":"5.54-5.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["bluez-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bluez-devel-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bluez-debuginfo-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bluez-debugsource-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bluez-cups-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bluez-libs-5.54-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["bluez-help-5.54-5.o